page.title: 12AMPFIELD WOOD
page.content: Ampfield Forest is both coniferous and deciduous.It belongs to two estates or landowners.The Forestry Commission were given it to look after in 1950.There are many different {trees}such as beech,hybrid larch, silver lime,silver birch,ash,oak, hawthorn,scots pine,horse_chestnut, sweet_chestnut,maple,white_beam and yew. There are also numerous wild { {flowers}in the wood such as tall fox_ gloves,cerise pink herb robert,white dead_nettle,fieldmouse_ear_chickweed, chickweed,yellow buttercups,pimpernel, brooklime,corn spurrey,tiny blue forget_me_nots,tufted vetch,prickly thistle,cat mint (herb),euphorbia, masses of cow parsley,cornflowers, violets,dandelions,bugle and lords and ladies.
